{"name": "django-modelcluster", "metadata": {"name": "django-modelcluster", "version": "6.3", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 5 - Production/Stable", "Environment :: Web Environment", "Framework :: Django", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: BSD License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3 :: Only", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9"], "home_page": "https://github.com/wagtail/django-modelcluster", "license": "BSD", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["pytz", "django"], "summary": "Django extension to allow working with 'clusters' of models as a single unit, independently of the database", "upload_time": 1708975610}, "documentation": ["# django-modelcluster\n\nIf you had a data model like this:\n\n```python\nclass Band(models.Model):\n    name = models.CharField(max_length=255)\n\nclass BandMember(models.Model):\n    band = models.ForeignKey('Band', related_name='members', on_delete=models.CASCADE)\n    name = models.CharField(max_length=255)\n```\n\nwouldn't it be nice if you could construct bundles of objects like this, independently of the database:\n\n```python\nbeatles = Band(name='The Beatles')\nbeatles.members = [\n    BandMember(name='John Lennon'),\n    BandMember(name='Paul McCartney'),\n]\n```\n\nUnfortunately, you can't. Objects need to exist in the database for foreign key relations to work:\n\n```python\nIntegrityError: null value in column \"band_id\" violates not-null constraint\n```\n\nBut what if you could? There are all sorts of scenarios where you might want to work with a 'cluster' of related objects, without necessarily holding them in the database: maybe you want to render a preview of the data the user has just submitted, prior to saving. Maybe you need to construct a tree of things, serialize them and hand them off to some external system. Maybe you have a workflow where your models exist in an incomplete 'draft' state for an extended time, or you need to handle multiple revisions, and you don't want to redesign your database around that requirement.\n\n**django-modelcluster** extends Django's foreign key relations to make this possible. It introduces a new type of relation, *ParentalKey*, where the related models are stored locally to the 'parent' model until the parent is explicitly saved. Up to that point, the related models can still be accessed through a subset of the QuerySet API:\n\n```python\nfrom modelcluster.models import ClusterableModel\nfrom modelcluster.fields import ParentalKey\n\n\nclass Band(ClusterableModel):\n    name = models.CharField(max_length=255)\n\nclass BandMember(models.Model):\n    band = ParentalKey('Band', related_name='members', on_delete=models.CASCADE)\n    name = models.CharField(max_length=255)\n\n\n>>> beatles = Band(name='The Beatles')\n>>> beatles.members = [\n...     BandMember(name='John Lennon'),\n...     BandMember(name='Paul McCartney'),\n... ]\n>>> [member.name for member in beatles.members.all()]\n['John Lennon', 'Paul McCartney']\n>>> beatles.members.add(BandMember(name='George Harrison'))\n>>> beatles.members.count()\n3\n>>> beatles.save()  # only now are the records written to the database\n```\n\nFor more examples, see the unit tests.\n\n## Many-to-many relations\n\nFor many-to-many relations, a corresponding *ParentalManyToManyField* is available:\n\n```python\nfrom modelcluster.models import ClusterableModel\nfrom modelcluster.fields import ParentalManyToManyField\n\nclass Movie(ClusterableModel):\n    title = models.CharField(max_length=255)\n    actors = ParentalManyToManyField('Actor', related_name='movies')\n\nclass Actor(models.Model):\n    name = models.CharField(max_length=255)\n\n\n>>> harrison_ford = Actor.objects.create(name='Harrison Ford')\n>>> carrie_fisher = Actor.objects.create(name='Carrie Fisher')\n>>> star_wars = Movie(title='Star Wars')\n>>> star_wars.actors = [harrison_ford, carrie_fisher]\n>>> blade_runner = Movie(title='Blade Runner')\n>>> blade_runner.actors.add(harrison_ford)\n>>> star_wars.actors.count()\n2\n>>> [movie.title for movie in harrison_ford.movies.all()]  # the Movie records are not in the database yet\n[]\n>>> star_wars.save()  # Star Wars now exists in the database (along with the 'actor' relations)\n>>> [movie.title for movie in harrison_ford.movies.all()]\n['Star Wars']\n```\n\nNote that `ParentalManyToManyField` is defined on the parent model rather than the related model, just as a standard `ManyToManyField` would be. Also note that the related objects - the `Actor` instances in the above example - must exist in the database before being associated with the parent record. (The `ParentalManyToManyField` allows the relations between Movies and Actors to be stored in memory without writing to the database, but not the `Actor` records themselves.)\n\n## Introspection\n\nIf you need to find out which child relations exist on a parent model - to create a deep copy of the model and all its children, say - use the `modelcluster.models.get_all_child_relations` function:\n\n```python\n>>> from modelcluster.models import get_all_child_relations\n>>> get_all_child_relations(Band)\n[<RelatedObject: tests:bandmember related to band>, <RelatedObject: tests:album related to band>]\n```\n\nThis includes relations that are defined on any superclasses of the parent model.\n\nTo retrieve a list of all ParentalManyToManyFields defined on a parent model, use `modelcluster.models.get_all_child_m2m_relations`:\n\n```python\n>>> from modelcluster.models import get_all_child_m2m_relations\n>>> get_all_child_m2m_relations(Movie)\n[<modelcluster.fields.ParentalManyToManyField: actors>]\n```\n"], "modules": [{"name": "modelcluster", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "modelcluster.utils", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "modelcluster.utils.get_model_field", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "model", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "name", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Returns a model field matching the supplied `name`, which can include\ndouble-underscores (`'__'`) to indicate relationship traversal - in which\ncase, the model field will be lookuped up from the related model.\n\nMultiple traversals for the same field are supported, but at this\nmoment in time, only traversal of many-to-one and one-to-one relationships\nis supported.\n\nDetails of any relationships traversed in order to reach the returned\nfield are made available as `field.traversals`. The value is a tuple of\n`TraversedRelationship` instances.\n\nRaises `FieldDoesNotExist` if the name cannot be mapped to a model field.\n"]}, {"name": "modelcluster.utils.extract_field_value", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "obj", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "key", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "pk_only", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "suppress_fielddoesnotexist", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "suppress_nullrelationshipvalueencountered", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Attempts to extract a field value from `obj` matching the `key` - which,\ncan contain double-underscores (`'__'`) to indicate traversal of relationships\nto related objects.\n\nFor keys that specify `ForeignKey` or `OneToOneField` field values, full\nrelated objects are returned by default. If only the primary key values are\nrequired ((.g. when ordering, or using `values()` or `values_list()`)),\ncall the function with `pk_only=True`.\n\nBy default, `FieldDoesNotExist` is raised if the key cannot be mapped to\na model field. Call the function with `suppress_fielddoesnotexist=True`\nto instead receive a `None` value when this occurs.\n\nBy default, `NullRelationshipValueEncountered` is raised if a `None`\nvalue is encountered while attempting to traverse relationships in order to\naccess further fields. Call the function with\n`suppress_nullrelationshipvalueencountered` to instead receive a `None`\nvalue when this occurs.\n"]}, {"name": "modelcluster.utils.sort_by_fields", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "items", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "fields", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Sort a list of objects on the given fields. The field list works analogously to\nqueryset.order_by(*fields): each field is either a property of the object,\nor is prefixed by '-' (e.g. '-name') to indicate reverse ordering."]}], "variables": [{"name": "modelcluster.utils.REL_DELIMETER", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "modelcluster.utils.ManyToManyTraversalError", "bases": ["ValueError"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "modelcluster.utils.NullRelationshipValueEncountered", "bases": ["Exception"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "modelcluster.utils.TraversedRelationship", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "modelcluster.utils.TraversedRelationship.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "from_model", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "field", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "modelcluster.utils.TraversedRelationship.field_name", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "modelcluster.utils.TraversedRelationship.to_model", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [{"name": "modelcluster.utils.TraversedRelationship.__slots__", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "modelcluster.contrib.taggit", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "modelcluster.contrib.taggit._ClusterTaggableManager", "bases": ["_TaggableManager"], "methods": [{"name": "modelcluster.contrib.taggit._ClusterTaggableManager.get_tagged_item_manager", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Return the manager that handles the relation from this instance to the tagged_item class.\nIf content_object on the tagged_item class is defined as a ParentalKey, this will be a\nDeferringRelatedManager which allows writing related objects without committing them\nto the database."]}, {"name": "modelcluster.contrib.taggit._ClusterTaggableManager.get_queryset", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "extra_filters", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "modelcluster.contrib.taggit._ClusterTaggableManager.add", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "*tags", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "modelcluster.contrib.taggit._ClusterTaggableManager.remove", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "*tags", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "modelcluster.contrib.taggit._ClusterTaggableManager.set", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "*args", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "modelcluster.contrib.taggit._ClusterTaggableManager.clear", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "modelcluster.contrib.taggit.ClusterTaggableManager", "bases": ["TaggableManager"], "methods": [{"name": "modelcluster.contrib.taggit.ClusterTaggableManager.__get__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "instance", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "model", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "modelcluster.contrib.taggit.ClusterTaggableManager.value_from_object", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "instance", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [{"name": "modelcluster.contrib.taggit.ClusterTaggableManager._need_commit_after_assignment", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "modelcluster.contrib", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "modelcluster.datetime_utils", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "modelcluster.datetime_utils.derive_from_value", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "value", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "expr", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "modelcluster.datetime_utils.derive_from_time", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "value", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "expr", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Mimics the behaviour of the `hour`, `minute` and `second` lookup\nexpressions that Django querysets support for `TimeField` and\n`DateTimeField`, by extracting the relevant value from an in-memory\n`time` or `datetime` value.\n"]}, {"name": "modelcluster.datetime_utils.derive_from_date", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "value", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "expr", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Mimics the behaviour of the `year`, `iso_year` `month`, `day`,\n`week`, `week_day`, `iso_week_day` and `quarter` lookup\nexpressions that Django querysets support for `DateField` and\n`DateTimeField` columns, by extracting the relevant value from an\nin-memory `date` or `datetime` value.\n"]}, {"name": "modelcluster.datetime_utils.derive_from_datetime", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "value", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "expr", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Mimics the behaviour of the `date`, `time` and other lookup\nexpressions that Django querysets support for `DateTimeField` columns,\nby extracting the relevant value from an in-memory `datetime` value.\n"]}], "variables": [{"name": "modelcluster.datetime_utils.TIMEFIELD_TRANSFORM_EXPRESSIONS", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "modelcluster.datetime_utils.DATEFIELD_TRANSFORM_EXPRESSIONS", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "modelcluster.datetime_utils.DATETIMEFIELD_TRANSFORM_EXPRESSIONS", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "modelcluster.datetime_utils.TRANSFORM_FIELD_TYPES", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "modelcluster.fields", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "modelcluster.fields.create_deferring_foreign_related_manager", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "related", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "original_manager_cls", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Create a DeferringRelatedManager class that wraps an ordinary RelatedManager\nwith 'deferring' behaviour: any updates to the object set (via e.g. add() or clear())\nare written to a holding area rather than committed to the database immediately.\nWriting to the database is deferred until the model is saved."]}, {"name": "modelcluster.fields.create_deferring_forward_many_to_many_manager", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "rel", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "original_manager_cls", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "modelcluster.fields.ChildObjectsDescriptor", "bases": ["ReverseManyToOneDescriptor"], "methods": [{"name": "modelcluster.fields.ChildObjectsDescriptor.__get__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "instance", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "instance_type", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "modelcluster.fields.ChildObjectsDescriptor.__set__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "instance", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "value", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "modelcluster.fields.ChildObjectsDescriptor.child_object_manager_cls", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "modelcluster.fields.ParentalKey", "bases": ["ForeignKey"], "methods": [{"name": "modelcluster.fields.ParentalKey.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "*args", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "modelcluster.fields.ParentalKey.check", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [{"name": "modelcluster.fields.ParentalKey.related_accessor_class", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "modelcluster.fields.ParentalManyToManyDescriptor", "bases": ["ManyToManyDescriptor"], "methods": [{"name": "modelcluster.fields.ParentalManyToManyDescriptor.__get__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "instance", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "instance_type", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "modelcluster.fields.ParentalManyToManyDescriptor.__set__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "instance", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "value", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "modelcluster.fields.ParentalManyToManyDescriptor.child_object_manager_cls", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "modelcluster.fields.ParentalManyToManyField", "bases": ["ManyToManyField"], "methods": [{"name": "modelcluster.fields.ParentalManyToManyField.contribute_to_class", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "cls", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "name", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "modelcluster.fields.ParentalManyToManyField.value_from_object", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "obj", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [{"name": "modelcluster.fields.ParentalManyToManyField.related_accessor_class", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "modelcluster.fields.ParentalManyToManyField._need_commit_after_assignment", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "modelcluster.tags", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "modelcluster.models", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "modelcluster.models.get_field_value", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "field", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "model", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "modelcluster.models.get_serializable_data_for_fields", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "model", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Return a serialised version of the model's fields which exist as local database\ncolumns (i.e. excluding m2m and incoming foreign key relations)"]}, {"name": "modelcluster.models.model_from_serializable_data", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "model", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "data", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "check_fks", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "strict_fks", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "modelcluster.models.get_all_child_relations", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "model", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Return a list of RelatedObject records for child relations of the given model,\nincluding ones attached to ancestors of the model"]}, {"name": "modelcluster.models.get_all_child_m2m_relations", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "model", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Return a list of ParentalManyToManyFields on the given model,\nincluding ones attached to ancestors of the model"]}], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "modelcluster.models.ClusterableModel", "bases": ["models.Model"], "methods": [{"name": "modelcluster.models.ClusterableModel.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "*args", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Extend the standard model constructor to allow child object lists to be passed in\nvia kwargs"]}, {"name": "modelcluster.models.ClusterableModel.save", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Save the model and commit all child relations."]}, {"name": "modelcluster.models.ClusterableModel.serializable_data", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "modelcluster.models.ClusterableModel.to_json", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "modelcluster.models.ClusterableModel.from_serializable_data", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cls", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "data", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "check_fks", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "strict_fks", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Build an instance of this model from the JSON-like structure passed in,\nrecursing into related objects as required.\nIf check_fks is true, it will check whether referenced foreign keys still\nexist in the database.\n- dangling foreign keys on related objects are dealt with by either nullifying the key or\ndropping the related object, according to the 'on_delete' setting.\n- dangling foreign keys on the base object will be nullified, unless strict_fks is true,\nin which case any dangling foreign keys with on_delete=CASCADE will cause None to be\nreturned for the entire object."]}, {"name": "modelcluster.models.ClusterableModel.from_json", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cls", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "json_data", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "check_fks", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "strict_fks", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "modelcluster.models.ClusterableModel.copy_child_relation", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "child_relation", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "target", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "commit", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "append", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Copies all of the objects in the accessor_name to the target object.\n\nFor example, say we have an event with speakers (my_event) and we need to copy these to another event (my_other_event):\n\n    my_event.copy_child_relation('speakers', my_other_event)\n\nBy default, this copies the child objects without saving them. Set the commit paremter to True to save the objects\nbut note that this would cause an exception if the target object is not saved.\n\nThis will overwrite the child relation on the target object. This is to avoid any issues with unique keys\nand/or sort_order. If you want it to append. set the `append` parameter to True.\n\nThis method returns a dictionary mapping the child relation/primary key on the source object to the new object created for the\ntarget object."]}, {"name": "modelcluster.models.ClusterableModel.copy_all_child_relations", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "target", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "exclude", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "commit", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "append", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Copies all of the objects in all child relations to the target object.\n\nThis will overwrite all of the child relations on the target object.\n\nSet exclude to a list of child relation accessor names that shouldn't be copied.\n\nThis method returns a dictionary mapping the child_relation/primary key on the source object to the new object created for the\ntarget object."]}, {"name": "modelcluster.models.ClusterableModel.copy_cluster", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "exclude_fields", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Makes a copy of this object and all child relations.\n\nIncludes all field data including child relations and parental many to many fields.\n\nDoesn't include non-parental many to many.\n\nThe result of this method is unsaved."]}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [{"name": "modelcluster.models.ClusterableModel.Meta", "bases": [], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "modelcluster.models.ClusterableModel.Meta.abstract", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "modelcluster.forms", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "modelcluster.forms.transientmodelformset_factory", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "model", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "formset", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "modelcluster.forms.childformset_factory", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "parent_model", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "model", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "form", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "formset", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "fk_name", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "fields", "type": null, "defau